    {
      "id": "zD0lp3Uid00nYbMz34lMf",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2511.105046404762,
      "y": 2322.3373648837664,
      "width": 866.7001953125,
      "height": 2041.2,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#e9ecef",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b18",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1899571991,
      "version": 12,
      "versionNonce": 961593529,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1781295861333,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Recommended Build Phases\n\nPhase 1: Portfolio + Inquiry MVP\nBuild:\nHome page\nPaintings gallery\nPainting detail pages\nAbout page\nContact page\nInquiry form\nEmail sending\nSEO metadata\nResponsive design\nBasic analytics\nNo database, no cart, no payment.\n\nPhase 2: Better Content Management\nAdd one of:\nKeep developer-managed data if updates are rare.\nAdd a CMS if your mom should edit paintings herself.\nAdd Supabase/Postgres if you want to learn \ndatabase-backed full-stack development.\n\nPhase 3: Direct Purchase\nAdd:\nDatabase\nOrder records\nPayment provider\nPayment webhooks\nSold/reserved status handling\nAdmin view for orders/inquiries\nFor Norway-first, prefer Vipps MobilePay ePayment.\n\nPhase 4: Mature E-commerce\nOnly if needed:\nCart\nMultiple-item checkout\nShipping rules\nDiscount codes\nInventory reservation timers\nCustomer accounts\nAdmin dashboard",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Recommended Build Phases\n\nPhase 1: Portfolio + Inquiry MVP\nBuild:\nHome page\nPaintings gallery\nPainting detail pages\nAbout page\nContact page\nInquiry form\nEmail sending\nSEO metadata\nResponsive design\nBasic analytics\nNo database, no cart, no payment.\n\nPhase 2: Better Content Management\nAdd one of:\nKeep developer-managed data if updates are rare.\nAdd a CMS if your mom should edit paintings herself.\nAdd Supabase/Postgres if you want to learn \ndatabase-backed full-stack development.\n\nPhase 3: Direct Purchase\nAdd:\nDatabase\nOrder records\nPayment provider\nPayment webhooks\nSold/reserved status handling\nAdmin view for orders/inquiries\nFor Norway-first, prefer Vipps MobilePay ePayment.\n\nPhase 4: Mature E-commerce\nOnly if needed:\nCart\nMultiple-item checkout\nShipping rules\nDiscount codes\nInventory reservation timers\nCustomer accounts\nAdmin dashboard",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.35
    },
    {
      "id": "bAzyT0YCvqG_zrlvqDWhQ",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 3729.438379738095,
      "y": 2326.504031550433,
      "width": 1355.1844482421875,
      "height": 1312.2,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#0c8599",
      "backgroundColor": "#e9ecef",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b19",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 939947351,
      "version": 8,
      "versionNonce": 656115353,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1781296015581,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Test Plan\n\nFor v1, test these scenarios:\nGallery renders all paintings from the data file.\nPainting detail page works for valid slugs.\nInvalid painting slug returns a proper not-found page.\nSold paintings cannot show the same call-to-action as available paintings.\nInquiry form rejects missing or invalid email/name/message.\nInquiry form includes the painting reference in the email.\nSuccessful inquiry shows a confirmation message.\nEmail API failure shows a friendly error.\nPages work on mobile and desktop.\nImages load with good layout stability.\nSEO metadata exists for home, gallery, and painting detail pages.\n\n\nAssumptions and Defaults\n\nMain market is Norway.\nFirst version uses inquiry-first sales, not direct checkout.\nPainting content is developer-managed at first.\nNo user accounts in v1.\nNo shopping cart in v1.\nNo database in v1.\nUse Next.js + TypeScript as the core app.\nUse server-side form handling inside the Next.js app instead of a separate backend.\nAdd Vipps MobilePay only when direct payment becomes a real requirement.",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Test Plan\n\nFor v1, test these scenarios:\nGallery renders all paintings from the data file.\nPainting detail page works for valid slugs.\nInvalid painting slug returns a proper not-found page.\nSold paintings cannot show the same call-to-action as available paintings.\nInquiry form rejects missing or invalid email/name/message.\nInquiry form includes the painting reference in the email.\nSuccessful inquiry shows a confirmation message.\nEmail API failure shows a friendly error.\nPages work on mobile and desktop.\nImages load with good layout stability.\nSEO metadata exists for home, gallery, and painting detail pages.\n\n\nAssumptions and Defaults\n\nMain market is Norway.\nFirst version uses inquiry-first sales, not direct checkout.\nPainting content is developer-managed at first.\nNo user accounts in v1.\nNo shopping cart in v1.\nNo database in v1.\nUse Next.js + TypeScript as the core app.\nUse server-side form handling inside the Next.js app instead of a separate backend.\nAdd Vipps MobilePay only when direct payment becomes a real requirement.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.35
    }
  ],
